Description: Double ovolo moulding. On the front side two equally sized and straight ovolo mouldings overlap. One transitions into a plain surface, whilst the other accompanies the rim of a cove. Light grey marble. Both ends of the moulding strings, as well as the backside of the fragment are fractured.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis) (Attributed by Petrie to the 'second temple of Apollo'.)
Curator's comments: There are insufficient parallels to interpret this fragment. One might consider the cover profile of an altar that ends a corner acroteria of the Milesian type, however, all known examples of this type have only one ovolo moulding (Koenigs 1980, 68ff. No. 2. 9a.)
